HEADWORD: Tacksman
<hw>Tacks"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Tacksmen</plw> <pr>(?)</pr>.</plu> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>One
who holds a tack or lease from another; a tenant, or lessee.</def>
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>tacksmen</qex>, who formed what may be called the
⟦ldquo⟧peerage⟦rdquo⟧ of the little community, must be the captains.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tacky</ent>⟦br⟧
